{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it an offence to leave a dog unattended for 12 hours",
        "additional_details": "As far as I am aware the laws on domestic pets have only changed once since 1911 and currently do not reflect the expected care of duty a responsible and caring dog owner would have for their family pet dog.",
        "background": "As a nation of dog lovers, I\u2019m sure people would be horrified to discover that is allowed by law to leave a dog unattended to for 24 hours. This is a form of neglect and causes stress to the dog. Dogs need companionship, stimulation and be able to toilet suitably. Please help me in changing this.",
